	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Super-Hampster wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I didn't rout the audio through an expansion port pin because my T89 adapter didn't have the middle pins on the card edge. I had to use a wire. Otherwise I would have routed it through an expansion port pin. I considered purchasing an adapter that did have the middle pins, but I didn't want to spend what they were selling it for at the time when I already had an adapter handy.</div>
<br />
<br />I have an T89 too and it actually HAS one of the expansion pins unused.
<br />So I used pin 52 on my T89, which goes to the expansion port too, but does not match the layout used on the Power Pak. I simply added a jumper which connects pin 52 and the pin used by the Power Pak.
<br />
